{{Infobox Indian politician|name=Amol Ratan Balwadkar|office=[[Pune Municipal Corporation]]|native_name=अमोल रतन बालवडकर|native_name_lang=[[Marathi]]|constituency=Baner-Balewadi-Pashan-Sutarwadi-Panchvati|birth_name=Amol Ratan Balwadkar|birth_date={{birth date and age|df=yes|1987|02|17}}|birth_place=[[Pune]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]|nationality=Indian|profession=[[Social Work]] [[Politician]]|website=www.amolbalwadkar.in|image=}}

== Biography==
'''Amol Ratan Balwadkar''' ([[Marathi language|Marathi]] : अमोल रतन बालवडकर ) is a corporator in [[Pune Municipal Corporation]] from [[Baner]]-[[Balewadi]] ward of [[Pune]] as a member of [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]. On March 2017, he won the corporation election. He is also general secretary of Bhartiya Janata Party Yuva Morcha Pune city.<ref name="Punekar News 2017">{{cite web | title=BJP corporator Amol Balwadkar sent to jail for threatening policeman | website=Punekar News | date=3 December 2017 | url=http://www.punekarnews.in/bjp-corporator-amol-balwadkar-sent-to-jail-for-threatening-policeman/ | language=hi | access-date=3 December 2017}}</ref><ref name="http://www.hindustantimes.com/ 2017">{{cite web | title=Bombay HC says new buildings cannot come up in two Pune localities until water issues are solved | website=hindustantimes.com/ | date=23 June 2017 | url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/mumbai-news/bombay-hc-says-new-buildings-cannot-come-up-in-two-pune-localities-until-water-issues-are-solved/story-p46t27TN1mNVevHxuNUALM.html | access-date=3 December 2017}}</ref><ref name="The Indian Express 2017">{{cite web | title=Water shortage: HC directive to Pune civic body | website=The Indian Express | date=24 June 2017 | url=http://indianexpress.com/article/cities/pune/water-shortage-hc-directive-to-pune-civic-body-4719292/ | access-date=3 December 2017}}</ref>

