{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox settlement--> | official_name = Migonys |coordinates = {{coord|55|44|40|N|25|02|20|E|region:LT|display=inline,title}} | |pushpin_map =Lithuania |pushpin_label_position = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none --> |pushpin_map_caption = Location of Migonys |pushpin_mapsize = |image_map = |map_caption = |image_shield = |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{LTU}} |subdivision_type1=[[Regions of Lithuania|Ethnographic&nbsp;region]] |subdivision_name1=[[Aukštaitija]] |subdivision_type2=[[Counties of Lithuania|County]]| |subdivision_name2=[[File:Panevezys County flag.svg|20px]] [[Panevėžys County]] |subdivision_type3=[[List of municipalities of Lithuania|Municipality]] |subdivision_name3=[[Kupiškis district municipality]] |subdivision_type4=[[Elderships of Lithuania|Eldership]]| subdivision_name4=Šimoniai elderate | established_title= First mentioned | established_date = 1594 | established_date2 = | population_total = 106 | population_as_of = 2011 | population_blank1 = |timezone=[[Eastern European Time|EET]] |utc_offset=+2 |timezone_DST=[[Eastern European Summer Time|EEST]] |utc_offset_DST=+3 }}
'''Migonys''' is a village in the [[Kupiškis district municipality]], [[Lithuania]]. According to the 2011 census, it had 106 inhabitants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://statistics.bookdesign.lt/table_125_09.htm?lang=en|title=2011 census|publisher=Statistikos Departamentas (Lithuania)|accessdate=August 19, 2017}}</ref> The village celebrated its 400th anniversary in 1924. There is a [[Hillfort#Lithuania|hill-fort]] and 36 [[tumulus|tumuli]] (28 survive) in the vicinity of the village.
18th century Lithuanian architect [[Laurynas Gucevičius]] was born in Migonys.
