{{Pulitzer}} The '''Pulitzer Prize for Editorial Cartoons''' is one of the fourteen [[Pulitzer Prize]]s that is annually awarded for Journalism. It has been awarded since 1922 for a distinguished [[editorial cartoon]] or portfolio of cartoons published during the year, characterized by originality, editorial effectiveness, quality of drawing, and pictorial effect.
Since 1980, finalists (usually two) have been announced in addition to the winner.<ref name="prize" />
