iphant|Pat Oliphant}} | ''[[The Denver Post]]'' | "For 'They Won't Get Us To The Conference Table...Will They?' Published February 1, 1966." |- | align=center | 1968 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Eugene Gray|Payne|Eugene Payne}} | ''[[The Charlotte Observer]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning in 1967." |- | align=center | 1969 ! scope=row | {{sortname|John|Fischetti}} | ''[[Chicago Daily News]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning in 1968." |- | align=center | 1970 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Thomas F.|Darcy}} | ''[[Newsday]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning during 1969." |- | align=center | 1971 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Paul|Conrad}} | ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning during 1970." |- | align=center | 1972 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Jeffrey K.|MacNelly|Jeff MacNelly}} | ''[[The Richmond News Leader|Richmond News-Leader]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning during 1971." |- | align=center | 1973 ! scope=row colspan=3 | ''No award given.'' |- | align=center | 1974 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Paul|Szep}} | ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' | "For his editorial cartooning during 1973." |- | align=center | 1975 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Garry|Trudeau}} | [[Universal Press Syndicate]] | "For his cartoon strip ''[[Doonesbury]]''." |- | align=center | 1976 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Tony|Auth}} | ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' | "For 'O beautiful for spacious skies, For amber waves of grain,' published on July 22, 1975." |- | align=center | 1977 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Paul|Szep}} | ''[[The Boston Globe]]'' | <!--none--> |- | align=center | 1978 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Jeffrey K.|MacNelly|Jeff MacNelly}} | ''[[The Richmond News Leader|Richmond News Leader]]'' | <!--none--> |- | align=center | 1979 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Herbert L.|Block|Herblock}} | ''[[The Washington Post]]'' | "For the body of his work." |- | align=center | 1980 ! scope=row | {{sortname|Don|Wright|Don Wright (cartoonist)}} | ''[[The Miami News]]'' | <!--none--> |- | align=center | 1981 ! scope=row | {