==Repeat winners==
Through 2017, eighteen people have won the Editorial Cartooning Pulitzer twice, and five of those have won it three times.
{| class="wikitable sortable" ! scope=col | Name ! scope=col | {{abbr|No.|Number of wins}} ! scope=col class=unsortable | Years won |- | {{sortname|Rollin|Kirby}} | align=center | 3 | 1922, 1925, 1929 |- | {{sortname|Edmund|Duffy}} | align=center | 3 | 1931, 1934, 1940 |- | {{sortname|Herbert L.|Block|Herblock}} | align=center | 3 | 1942, 1954, 1979 |- | {{sortname|Paul|Conrad}} | align=center | 3 | 1964, 1971, 1984 |- | {{sortname|Jeff|MacNelly}} | align=center | 3 | 1972, 1978, 1985 |}
The other repeat winners are Steve Breen, Jay N. "Ding" Darling, Daniel R. Fitzpatrick, Walt Handelsman, Nelson Harding, David Horsey, Mike Luckovich, Bill Mauldin, Jim Morin, Michael Ramirez, Vaughn Shoemaker, Paul Szep, and Don Wright.
[[Nelson Harding]] won the prize consecutively in 1927 and 1928.<ref name=prize/>
